<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:05PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Pike County
through 545 PM CDT...
At 505 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Daisy State Park, or 11 miles northwest of Murfreesboro, moving
southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Murfreesboro...                   Daisy...
Narrows Dam...                    Daisy State Park...
Nathan...                         Highland in Pike County...
New Hope in Pike County...        Pike City...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
